 :tx/rationale "Create task: EPIC: Action-Centric Projection (ACP) — Unification of output pipeline, guidance system, and budget management (INV-BUDGET-007..009, ADR-BUDGET-005..007). BACKGROUND: The truncation problem revealed a fundamental architectural error: braid treats output as CONTENT to be compressed, but from prompt-optimization theory, output is ACTIVATION — a field configuration over the agent's latent manifold. ACP decomposes every output into Action (never truncated, R(t) recommendation, ~10 tokens), Context (scales with budget, precedence-ordered), and Evidence (on-demand via pointer). This eliminates truncation by construction — the Action is structurally first and always complete. The guidance system IS the projection function: R(t) provides the Action, the budget system determines Context fill level. Four activation strategies map to k* regimes: Demonstrate (high k*, ~300 tokens), Navigate (medium, ~100), Imperative (low, ~20), Signal (critical, ~5). SUBSUMES: t-f1b1 (Budget Pipeline EPIC), t-17edf3df (task pyramid), t-ad704639 (topology pyramid), t-1029e16f (short-title). EXTENDS: t-83ce (LLM Surface), t-846524e2 (Ergonomics). KEY INVARIANT: At every budget level >= MIN_OUTPUT, the output contains a complete, actionable recommendation. TRACES TO: INV-BUDGET-001..006, INV-INTERFACE-001, INV-GUIDANCE-001, INV-GUIDANCE-010, ADR-BUDGET-003 (rate-distortion), ADR-INTERFACE-002 (demonstration style), ADR-INTERFACE-011 (API-as-prompt)."
